## M20b(5/5) negative: missing method on a parameterized receiver.
##
## Before this commit, `b.missing()` on `b: Box(Int)` fell through to
## a silent unknown or the placeholder "(unknown)" type name in the
## diagnostic — because `synthInstanceCall`'s error path only handled
## `.nominal`, not `.parameterized_nominal`. Per GPT-5.5 M20b
## post-implementation review, the new `nominalSymOfReceiver` helper
## handles both uniformly so generic receivers get clean diagnostics.
##
## EXPECTED: sema error: no method `missing` on type `Box`.

type Box(T)
  value: T

sub main()
  b: Box(Int) = Box(value: 5)
  print(b.missing())
